main event: An observer sighted an unidentified object in the sky in Erlanger, Kentucky on October 26, 1965, which they believed to be a satellite.
interesting points: The object looked like a regular star, but was closer and moved in a straight line across the sky.
The object took about 5 minutes to cross the sky in a northeasterly direction.
The observer was uncertain if the object was a satellite or something else.
The report mentions that there are 30 satellites visible to the naked eye.
The report also mentions that the object was not Echo I, II, or Pegasus I, II, III.
sighted object: An unidentified object that looked like a star but was closer and moved across the sky
